content.description: Start on the two side pulls with your feet under the over hang. Make an awkward move up, then it’s easy to the top.
content.protection: a pad and some thing to cover the rock at the start
content.location: Wright after the gate take a right walk for 20 feet you’ll see a overhang (the cent of money) take a left step over the fence and you will see it.

content.description: Little nubs on a slightly inclined face. On a 5 foot ledge before another small fall, so a top out fall would be a little sketchy. Starts on two obvious nubs above the little over hang then continues up to the right a little bit.
content.location: Take a right after the first gate (about a mile up the canyon) and follow a clear trail to the rock face (The Cent of Money). Then turn right over the log at the end of the fence and nubs bunny is rite there.

content.description: Start on a slightly protruding block with an undercling and a good-ish jug. Then move up to a good sloper pinch and from there go to the good crimp. Dynamic moves to a good hold that's facing the wrong way. Jugs to awkward top out around the corner.
content.protection: 2 pads but it will work with 1
content.location: Take a right just after the gate (about a mile into the canyon) you will find 2 rock faces on ether side of a slightly elevated flat spot The cent on money is on the right.
